      {
        "paragraph_index": 0,
        "text": "Short answer: SRD‑46 contains no stability-constant measurements at 200 °C and does not index pressure (so a 50 bar filter is not available). A broad sweep of all entries with recorded temperatures returned no measurements at or near 200 °C; the highest‑temperature records we found were ≤ ~75 °C for a few systems (e.g., H+ with adenosine‑5'‑(trihydrogendi…), Mg2+ with the same ligand, Cf3+ with hydroxyacetic acid, and Cr3+ with an azo‑phenylsulfonate), and none reported pressure.",
